10:
Yeah, it's just a scratch.
I can still fight, no problem.
13:
Ahem, Nimbus.
May I ask you a question?
18:
When you die. What do you want to 
leave behind? And to whom?
23:
Wow... You've got great bedside
manners, you know that?
25:
Not that I haven't given it some
thought or anything...
27:
So. If your time comes unexpectedly.
You'll be okay? You won't have regrets?
30:
What, it's like you're half-expectin' me to
say I'm not ready to go. Just spit it out.
33:
If you're scared of death. But you don't
prepare for it. You'll only end up leaving regret behind.
35:
You need to decide what to pass on.
Sooner rather than later. Because the
reaper. Will not wait.
38:
Fair enough. Let's just say I was more
than ready to face him before, but he
didn't come for me.
40:
So I'll do what I want, when I want. And if
I go down along the way, well, I'm sure
someone'll come pick up my bones.
44:
I see. You carry few burdens, Nimbus.
I doubt you'll have any regrets.
47:
Guess we'll find out. But now it's your
turn—are you ready to see the big man
in the sky?
51:
...Yes. I have to be. There are people
I must see again.
53:
So. If I die. I need you. To visit them
in my place. And tell them I loved them.
56:
Humph. That's not a plan I can get
behind.
64:
You want those to be your last words?
I can barely stand to hear 'em myself.
66:
Maybe it's because you're too young to
understand, but you'd better handle
your business while you're still
breathing.
74:
Death, shmeath. You're not gonna die,
okay, Falsche? Not while I'm around.
82:
Humph. Just watch me. Yeesh,
"be prepared"—you sound like you're
selling insurance...
86:
Very well. Promise me you won't die
either, okay?
88:
...I don't want anyone else to leave me
behind.
91:
Sure thing... As long as you keep busting
your hide to stay alive! Now, let's move!
96:
Lead the way... Mom. Dad. It looks like I'll
come see you while I'm alive after all.
